    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>, <hi rend="italic">San
                                Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11, 1890</date>.
                            (Received August 11.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Mizner informs Mr. Blaine that the Salvadorian Government, in accordance
                        with our minister’s demand, hoisted the flag of the United States over our
                        consulate in San Salvador, firing a salute of twenty-one <pb facs="0169" n="65" xml:id="pg_65"/> guns; reinstated the consul in his office and
                        guarantied his rights. He reports the satisfactory conclusion of the
                        incident by an adequate letter of apology from the Salvadorian minister for
                        foreign affairs.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
